---
title: Satellite Events & Initiatives
---
body:

Satellite events and initiatives are community-organized activities that take
place around PyCon DE & PyData — before, during, or after the conference days
(19–24 April 2027 in Heidelberg). They are run by and for the community and
are open to everyone; a conference ticket is usually not required.

Past and ongoing examples include the Feminist AI Hackerspace, the Django
Girls workshop, PyLadies meetups, and the open-source Sprints & Hackathons.

## Propose a satellite event or initiative

We welcome proposals from community groups, open-source projects, and
individuals. To propose a satellite event or initiative, [contact
us](/contact/) with the following details:

* **What** — the name and a short description of your event or initiative
* **Who** — the organizers and the audience you want to reach
* **When** — preferred date(s) relative to the conference week
* **Where** — your own venue, or whether you need help finding space
* **What you need from us** — promotion on this site, scheduling
  coordination, contacts, or anything else

The conference team reviews proposals on a rolling basis and will get back
to you with next steps. Accepted events are featured on the front page and
promoted through the conference channels.
